    "Physics Constraints": "The model must satisfy the heat equation in the interior, the Dirichlet condition at x=0, the Neumann condition at x=L, and the initial condition. Physics-informed loss terms: residual of the PDE (∂u/∂t - α ∂²u/∂x²) over collocation points in the domain; boundary loss for u(0,t) - T0; boundary loss for -k ∂u/∂x(L,t) - q; initial loss for u(x,0) - f(x). The PDE residual enforces conservation of energy; boundary conditions ensure uniqueness.",
    "Model Choice": "A physics-informed neural network (PINN) is appropriate because it can incorporate all constraints directly into the loss function without discretizing the domain. The network takes (x,t) as inputs and outputs u(x,t). A fully connected feedforward network with 4-6 hidden layers, 50-100 neurons per layer, and tanh activation is suitable for smooth solutions. This choice handles mixed boundary conditions naturally and works with limited or no data, relying on physics constraints.",
